Welcome To Triaxis GNU/Linux Handbook RISC-V
This Guide Will Help You To Install Triaxis Correctly

1 enter https://ubuntu.com/download/risc-v/canonical-built#allwinner-nezha then download ubuntu server lts iso then Before You Install Flash Ubuntu Server Iso With Rufus Etcher Or Ventoy
Make Sure That There Are No important Files Inside the USB Drive Then Backup Your Data On Your System Because It Will Erase Your Partition Drive After Installing Triaxis
For Rufus There are both ISO mode (the default, file-copy method) and DD mode (a block-level copy method) options
and I Would Recommend To Use dd mode Because On ISO mode it Can fail Because ISO mode partitions and formats the USB like a standard drive

2 Boot from the Ubuntu Server ISO
  Theres Password on su -
  I Would recommend to change the password to your password using sudo passwd root for example triaxis or become root using sudo -i
  Press Ctrl+Alt+F2 to switch to a shell.
3 Partition the Disk Using cfdisk fdisk parted etc
  cfdisk /dev/sda
  Create partitions:

4 EFI (if UEFI): 512MB, type EFI System.
  Root (/): rest of disk, type Linux filesystem.
  Swap: optional, type Linux swap.
  Write changes and quit.

5 Format Partitions
  mkfs.ext4 /dev/sda2     # root
  mkswap /dev/sda3        # swap
  mkfs.fat -F32 /dev/sda1 # EFI (if UEFI)

6 Mount Target System
  mount /dev/sda2 /mnt
  mkdir /mnt/boot
  mkdir /mnt/boot/efi
  mount /dev/sda1 /mnt/boot/efi
  swapon /dev/sda3

7 Bootstrap Base System
  debootstrap --arch amd64 focal /mnt http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu

8 Chroot Into New System

  mount --bind /dev /mnt/dev
  mount --bind /proc /mnt/proc
  mount --bind /sys /mnt/sys
  chroot /mnt

9 Configure System
  Inside chroot:
  echo "myhostname" > /etc/hostname
  nano /etc/hosts   # add 127.0.0.1 myhostname

10 Set up networking:
   apt install net-tools ifupdown

11 Install Kernel & Essentials
   apt install linux-image-generic grub-pc sudo vim

12 Install Bootloader
   For BIOS:
   grub-install /dev/sda
   update-grub

13 For UEFI:
   apt install grub-efi
   grub-install --target=x86_64-efi --efi-directory=/boot/efi --bootloader-id=ubuntu
   update-grub

14 Create User
   adduser yourname
   usermod -aG sudo yourname

15 Exit & Reboot
   exit
   umount -R /mnt
   swapoff -a
   reboot

